  "title": "Production Operator / Technician #81260",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Manufacturing</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Production Operator / Technician</strong></li><li>Working Location: Tai Seng</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Mon – Fri, 8.00am – 5.45pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $2,300 + OT + AWS + Performance Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform mechanical assembly tasks to support production projects, including assembling wire harnesses and different types of cable assemblies (e.g., multi-core, coaxial, power, and flat cables).</li><li>Assemble, modify, rework, and/or reassemble production parts by following drawings, pick tickets, process documents, and/or verbal instructions.</li><li>Prepare and use basic hand tools and machines, including (but not limited to) power screwdrivers, rulers, soldering irons, clamp machines, heat guns, solder pots, crimpers, pinning machines, and automatic wire strippers.</li><li>Clean parts before production use when required.</li><li>Identify wires using basic colour-code sequences.</li><li>Take part in first production runs for new products.</li><li>Support cycle counting, inventory handling, and inventory transactions by following established material procedures.</li><li>Take part in continuous improvement and team activities and maintain good working relationships with team members.</li><li>Maintain good working knowledge of machines and assembly methods used in this or similar industries.</li><li>Meet daily production output and quality requirements.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Able to read, understand, and follow Work Instructions for assembling harnesses, cables, and other assigned tasks.</li><li>Able to perform crimping and soldering tasks.</li><li>Experience in detailed hand assembly in a paced production line environment.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81260 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
